The food here has taken a sudden turn for the worse. The sandwiches used to be the best in the neighborhood but now they are unrecognizably disappointing. A BLT with one slice of bacon and a pound of mayonnaise is a crime. The tomato slices look like scraps, they are mostly just tomato skin. The bread is even bad, it is way too thin to stay together and it looks like it was thrown in a toaster for thirty seconds. It is difficult to imagine someone thinking that a customer would be happy paying for something like this. The coffee is still good but anything more than a bagel with cream cheese is going to be a mess.  The old kitchen staff was carrying this place, there is no longer any reason to come here.
